Secretary of State Mike Pompeo held a press briefing to discuss the upcoming summit between President Trump and North Korean leader Kim Jong Un. Pompeo highlighted the Trump administration's commitment to addressing the threat posed by North Korea's weapons of mass destruction and ballistic missile programs. He discussed the "maximum pressure campaign" that was enacted to set the conditions for North Korea to make a strategic decision to denuclearize. Pompeo also mentioned that North Korea has confirmed its willingness to denuclearize and that preparations for the summit are underway. He emphasized that the United States will not accept anything less than complete, verifiable, and irreversible denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. Pompeo expressed hope for a future of friendship and collaboration between the United States and North Korea. During the briefing, Pompeo also addressed questions about progress in narrowing the gap on denuclearization, trust in Kim Jong Un, negotiations, security guarantees, and disagreements within the administration.